OL,3,CSpeaker says he gave information to
OL,4,Cpolice about Lord Mandelson ahead of
OL,5,Carrest
OL,7,FLawyers working for Mandelson said on
OL,8,FTuesday that his arrest was "prompted
OL,9,Fby a baseless suggestion that he was
OL,10,Fplanning to leave the country and take
OL,11,Fup permanent residence abroad".
OL,13,F"There is absolutely no truth
OL,14,Fwhatsoever in any such suggestion. We
OL,15,Fhave asked the MPS for the evidence
OL,16,Frelied upon to justify the arrest,"
OL,17,Fthey said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
